Store signal signing key into <code>~/signal-keys.asc</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
kwrite ~/signal-keys.asc
}}

Create a file.

{{CodeSelect|code=
kwrite ~/signal-start
}}

Paste the following text.

<pre>
#!/bin/bash
set -x
set -e
cat signal-keys.asc | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt xenial main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/signal-xenial.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install signal-desktop
signal-desktop
</pre>

Make executable.

{{CodeSelect|code=
chmod +x ~/signal-start
}}

Install and start Signal from command line.

{{CodeSelect|code=
~/signal-start
}}
